  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Corruption\n- Basel Anti-Money Laundering Standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Transaction Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Compliance Measures\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious activities\n- Financial institution screening\n- Enhanced background checks\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n5. Specific Sectors Covered\n- Banking\n- Real estate\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Casino and gambling industries\n- Securities markets\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes by establishing comprehensive regulatory standards and enforcement mechanisms.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering legal frameworks?",
